WEBVTT

00:02.069 --> 00:04.709
OLIVER:
My name is Oliver Queen.

00:04.872 --> 00:07.876
After five years on a hellish island...

00:08.041 --> 00:10.487
I have come home with only one goal:

00:11.078 --> 00:13.058
To save my city.

00:13.213 --> 00:16.683
But to do so, I can't be
the killer I once was.

00:18.385 --> 00:22.231
To honor my friend's memory,
I must be someone else.

00:23.323 --> 00:26.736
I must be something else.

00:27.694 --> 00:29.105
NARRATOR:
Previously on Arrow:

00:29.263 --> 00:32.767
Time to choose, Oliver,
who lives and who dies.

00:32.933 --> 00:35.345
- You got what you came for!
- Time's up.

00:35.536 --> 00:37.096
- No!
IVO: I guess you made your choice.

00:37.237 --> 00:38.272
[GUNSHOT]

00:38.438 --> 00:39.508
OLIVER:
No!

00:39.673 --> 00:40.947
Ivo killed Shade because of me.

00:41.108 --> 00:44.351
Nothing good comes from telling Slade
you think you're responsible...

00:44.511 --> 00:46.457
for the death of the woman he loved.

00:46.613 --> 00:50.288
The man who lulled.

00:50.517 --> 00:53.589
Not for long,
because we're gonna take the freighter.

00:53.854 --> 00:55.629
We're all gonna die here.

00:55.856 --> 00:57.233
Just like him.

00:57.457 --> 01:00.233
OLIVER: No, we're not.
I think I found our way onto the freighter.

01:03.230 --> 01:04.265
Parachute.

01:04.431 --> 01:07.935
- I'd like you to meet Slade Wilson.
- It's a pleasure to meet you...

01:09.770 --> 01:11.215
Mr. Queen.

01:16.109 --> 01:18.316
What are you doing here?

01:19.880 --> 01:23.919
Mr. Wilson just made a sizable contribution
to my campaign.

01:26.219 --> 01:27.323
How generous of him.

01:27.554 --> 01:31.092
Well, I felt compelled. And it was the
least that I could do for your mother.

01:31.258 --> 01:35.001
What this city needs
is a pro-business mayor like Moira...

01:35.162 --> 01:37.733
to spur growth through urban investment.

01:37.931 --> 01:42.607
And we were just discussing
how to combat the rising wage gap.

01:42.769 --> 01:45.750
And the answer lies
in your budget proposal.

01:46.173 --> 01:47.982
You know, when I look at your mother...

01:48.141 --> 01:51.179
I think about everything you
went through after the quake.

01:51.345 --> 01:53.791
All I can say is,
you and I have something in common.

01:53.947 --> 01:55.324
MOIRA:
What's that?

01:55.482 --> 01:58.292
I know how difficult it is
to pick yourself back up...

01:58.452 --> 02:00.591
when other people have written you off.

02:03.256 --> 02:04.428
Indeed.

02:07.160 --> 02:08.798
What's wrong, Mr. Queen?

02:08.961 --> 02:10.464
You look a little piqued.

02:11.465 --> 02:13.877
I'm fine, thank you.

02:17.671 --> 02:19.947
Ah. Thank you, dear.

02:20.107 --> 02:26.388
Oliver, Mr. Wilson was kind enough to bring
a bottle of authentic Australian rum.

02:29.349 --> 02:31.295
Will you join us in a drink?

02:32.886 --> 02:34.388
Yes, of course.

02:34.554 --> 02:36.363
Wonderful.

02:37.024 --> 02:38.731
What shall we drink to?

02:42.529 --> 02:44.167
To friendship.

02:52.239 --> 02:55.152
- Ah.
Delicious.

02:55.509 --> 02:59.480
Uh, this here is a beautiful piece.

02:59.813 --> 03:04.319
Tell me, does your family spend
much time on the water?

03:04.484 --> 03:05.758
No.

03:05.919 --> 03:09.264
Not since my late husband.

03:10.057 --> 03:11.695
I'm sorry, Moira. Forgive me.

03:11.858 --> 03:15.067
I do remember reading about that accident
in the paper.

03:16.229 --> 03:17.503
You were a brave soul.

03:18.265 --> 03:20.336
I don't like to talk about it.

03:21.001 --> 03:22.412
I can understand.

03:22.569 --> 03:26.574
All that time on that island.
It must have been hell for you.

03:30.277 --> 03:32.450
[PANTING]

03:49.029 --> 03:52.909
[GRUNTING]

04:19.559 --> 04:21.129
[SIGHS]

04:24.498 --> 04:26.774
- Shado would be proud.
- Thank you.

04:26.933 --> 04:29.743
But those trees don't move or shoot back.

04:29.903 --> 04:32.247
Mo's men on the freighter will.

04:32.405 --> 04:34.476
Then shoot first.

04:42.415 --> 04:45.760
SLADE: Mo's freighter is located here.
He keeps eight men on deck.

04:45.919 --> 04:49.696
Three on the starboard,
three on the port and two up on the bridge.

04:49.856 --> 04:52.928
But our bigger concern
are these GP-25 grenade launchers...

04:53.093 --> 04:56.097
- that they're walking around with.
- Do they have night vision?

04:56.263 --> 04:58.470
Not according to Blondie.

04:58.865 --> 05:00.367
[SNIFFS]

05:02.135 --> 05:03.637
That smells awful.

05:03.804 --> 05:06.785
- It'll taste even worse.
- But it'll work?

05:06.940 --> 05:11.150
I spent a year with Anthony Ivo.
I know how he thinks.

05:11.311 --> 05:12.346
It'll work.

05:18.885 --> 05:20.956
Hey, what about the Mirakuru?

05:21.121 --> 05:24.694
- What about it?
- Well, look, I mean, it can cure...

05:24.858 --> 05:26.565
I don't know, maybe anything.

05:26.726 --> 05:30.503
Maybe... Maybe it's a miracle drug.

05:32.365 --> 05:34.811
But ifs also something else.

05:35.569 --> 05:40.143
Something that people like Ivo
should never be allowed to control.

05:40.740 --> 05:43.516
What about Slade? He might not let us.

05:44.711 --> 05:47.214
Might not let you do what?

05:47.981 --> 05:49.983
You think we should destroy the Mirakuru.

05:50.417 --> 05:52.863
If this thing doesn't go our way...

05:53.920 --> 05:55.661
we can't let Ivo have it.

05:57.490 --> 05:59.401
You're right.

05:59.559 --> 06:01.505
We should burn it.

06:03.530 --> 06:07.273
SARA: Anthony devoted his
entire life to finding this.

06:08.101 --> 06:10.581
Nobody even thought it was real.

06:11.037 --> 06:13.278
It was his dream.

06:13.440 --> 06:15.215
OLIVER:
Did he ever say why?

06:15.375 --> 06:17.753
SARA:
He wanted to save the world.

06:20.413 --> 06:23.121
We need to talk about tomorrow.

06:24.084 --> 06:27.088
About what to do with Anthony
once we take the freighter.

06:27.254 --> 06:28.597
What do you mean?

06:29.256 --> 06:31.293
Slade wants to kill him.

06:31.458 --> 06:32.960
I'm not gonna let that happen.

06:33.126 --> 06:36.039
No, Slade wants to kill him for Shado.

06:37.197 --> 06:40.303
Oliver, you don't know him like I do.

06:40.467 --> 06:43.971
Look, if he's given the chance,
then he's gonna turn this around.

06:44.137 --> 06:46.947
He's gonna make Slade think
it's your fault that she's dead.

06:47.307 --> 06:50.117
That you chose to save me instead of her.

06:51.811 --> 06:53.552
You can't give him that chance.

06:57.450 --> 07:00.590
- Sara, I can't.
- You've killed before.

07:00.754 --> 07:03.496
That's not what you are talking about.
You are talking...

07:03.657 --> 07:06.160
about executing somebody in cold blood.

07:06.326 --> 07:09.170
Look, Slade has the Mirakuru in him.
He's unstable.

07:09.329 --> 07:13.573
If he loses control, if he snaps again,
then we're both dead.

07:16.803 --> 07:18.680
You have to kill Ivo.

07:30.016 --> 07:32.189
Who's thirsty?

07:32.352 --> 07:34.764
OLIVER: Where'd you get that?
- Who cares? Let's drink it.

07:34.921 --> 07:40.269
Ah, this is one of the few precious pieces
of cargo to survive the crash.

07:40.427 --> 07:44.102
Billy Wintergreen and I were planning
on saving it for a rainy day.

07:44.264 --> 07:49.680
But considering, God willing,
this is our last night on the island...

07:50.971 --> 07:52.951
To taking the freighter.

07:53.106 --> 07:55.780
To getting off this island forever.

07:56.276 --> 07:57.983
To Shado.

08:02.816 --> 08:05.023
OLIVER:
Mm.

08:06.386 --> 08:08.332
You know, if something happens
to me tomorrow...

08:08.488 --> 08:10.468
You can't think like that.

08:14.194 --> 08:16.140
If I don't make it...

08:18.198 --> 08:19.905
I need you to...

08:21.201 --> 08:23.977
To tell my mom and my sister...

08:24.637 --> 08:30.713
that I wasn't that same stupid kid
who got on that boat.

08:34.847 --> 08:37.328
Tell them I was different.

08:38.018 --> 08:39.496
Okay.

08:40.553 --> 08:42.828
Hey, and if I don't make it...

08:43.823 --> 08:46.326
tell my family that
I died on the Gambit.

08:47.093 --> 08:48.367
Why?

08:48.528 --> 08:50.701
Let them remember me the way that I was.

08:57.203 --> 08:58.409
[SIGHS]

08:58.571 --> 09:00.915
We should all get some sleep.

09:10.683 --> 09:12.594
I've missed you.

09:16.623 --> 09:18.296
Shado?

09:22.228 --> 09:23.730
How are you still alive?

09:23.930 --> 09:25.773
I'm not alive.

09:26.566 --> 09:28.068
Remember?

09:29.302 --> 09:30.872
I'm dead.

09:32.138 --> 09:35.085
Because you chose Sara over me.

09:38.111 --> 09:40.557
Why didn't you choose me?

09:41.815 --> 09:43.761
Why didn't you choose me?

09:44.417 --> 09:46.419
Why didn't you choose me?

09:48.154 --> 09:50.430
[GASPS]

09:50.590 --> 09:53.070
Rise and shine, kid. it's time.

10:50.216 --> 10:51.957
[SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

10:52.118 --> 10:53.995
[CHUCKLES]

10:54.154 --> 10:56.862
Better luck next time, Hendrik.

10:57.857 --> 11:00.064
HENDRIK:
You cheat.

11:00.226 --> 11:01.534
He cheats.

11:01.694 --> 11:03.674
MAN:
So do you.

11:04.731 --> 11:07.371
He just cheats better.

11:07.534 --> 11:09.741
Get up, preacher boy.

11:09.903 --> 11:12.247
I said, get up, coward.

11:19.746 --> 11:22.750
[INMATES YELLING]

11:27.053 --> 11:28.327
[YELLING STOPS]

11:39.699 --> 11:42.543
Ivo wants to see you.

11:44.904 --> 11:48.442
Have faith, my friend.
God will protect you.

11:48.608 --> 11:50.918
There is no God.

11:51.277 --> 11:53.279
If there was...

11:53.513 --> 11:54.890
he's not on this ship.

11:55.048 --> 11:57.892
IVO: How is she?
MAN [OVER RADIO]: I'm sorry, Anthony.

11:58.051 --> 12:00.292
I wish I had better news to give you...

12:00.453 --> 12:04.401
but her condition is progressing quicker
than we anticipated.

12:05.592 --> 12:07.629
Have you tried upping her dosage?

12:07.794 --> 12:13.301
Twice already, but we both know
modern medicine has its limitations.

12:13.533 --> 12:16.104
Oh, yes, I know quite well.

12:17.136 --> 12:18.945
Thank you, doctor.

12:27.280 --> 12:33.322
No. No, wait. Wait, Mr. Ivo.
My family is Bratva, Russian mafia.

12:33.486 --> 12:35.796
They pay millions for me.

12:35.955 --> 12:38.834
I'm sorry. I have very
little use for money.

12:38.992 --> 12:45.136
I do, however, require an eye
for my research.

12:45.298 --> 12:46.333
No.

13:15.762 --> 13:18.106
[FOOTSTEPS]

13:19.098 --> 13:21.476
Well, we don't have all day.

13:23.202 --> 13:24.875
There's a breeze.

13:52.131 --> 13:57.012
They're on the beach. Take them. Alive.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.342
What about him?

13:59.138 --> 14:00.549
Eh.

14:03.343 --> 14:07.018
They're coming. Two men. Armed.

14:10.083 --> 14:12.893
You know, when we first tried
to get off this island...

14:13.086 --> 14:15.362
it was as strangers.

14:17.323 --> 14:19.667
But now it's as brothers.

14:22.762 --> 14:24.935
See you on the freighter.

14:38.778 --> 14:40.052
There!

14:45.017 --> 14:47.725
[PANTING]

14:52.058 --> 14:53.128
[GRUNTS]

14:56.696 --> 14:59.973
You're lucky Ivo wants you alive.

15:04.704 --> 15:06.809
I told you I'd come back.

15:06.973 --> 15:10.921
Fantastic. We're saved.

15:15.314 --> 15:17.385
[SQUEAKING]

15:25.291 --> 15:26.964
FLYNN:
He likes you.

15:29.429 --> 15:31.500
Don't worry. He won't bite.

15:32.965 --> 15:34.239
Reverend Thomas Flynn.

15:35.735 --> 15:36.839
Oliver Queen.

15:38.137 --> 15:40.310
And this is Abraham.

15:42.141 --> 15:44.678
I remember you from before. You escaped.

15:44.844 --> 15:47.415
HENDRIK: With that blond whore.
- That's Hendrik.

15:47.980 --> 15:50.859
- He's a charmer.
HENDRIK: Yeah, I hope she rots in hell.

15:51.017 --> 15:53.122
Hey, Sara was a prisoner.

15:53.286 --> 15:55.664
Just like all of us.

15:56.355 --> 16:00.531
Right. Funny, I never heard her scream.

16:02.028 --> 16:05.805
- How long have you been here, Thomas?
- A little over a year.

16:06.199 --> 16:10.045
I was working as a missionary in Maliku
just off the coast of India.

16:10.203 --> 16:12.183
A ship docked there for supplies.

16:12.338 --> 16:18.778
Dr. Ivo asked me to come aboard
to administer last rights for a dying man.

16:19.645 --> 16:22.057
- My mistake.
- I'm sorry.

16:23.015 --> 16:24.358
Don't be.

16:24.517 --> 16:27.293
Can you imagine a better place
for a man in my line of work?

16:28.454 --> 16:29.728
[KEYS RATTLING]

16:35.695 --> 16:37.868
Hey, prochnost.

16:44.737 --> 16:46.410
IVO:
Mr. Queen.

16:46.572 --> 16:48.415
Welcome back.

16:48.574 --> 16:51.919
My men are still searching the beach
for your friend and Sara.

16:52.712 --> 16:54.419
They have the Mirakuru.

16:55.081 --> 16:58.756
So where are they?

16:59.919 --> 17:01.227
You go to hell.

17:01.888 --> 17:04.425
Maybe you'd like to rethink that.

17:12.198 --> 17:17.204
Ivo, you torture me all you want to,
I am never gonna tell you where they are.

17:17.369 --> 17:19.611
No, not willingly.

17:23.943 --> 17:25.115
What is that?

17:25.877 --> 17:28.791
Oh, this? See, this is sodium pentothal.

17:29.115 --> 17:31.755
Its more colloquial,
yet very descriptive name...

17:32.218 --> 17:33.788
is "truth serum."

17:33.953 --> 17:36.797
Wait, no. Wait, wait.
I'll tell you everything!

17:38.858 --> 17:40.269
Let's begin.

17:41.227 --> 17:43.935
[SLADE LAUGHING]

17:44.096 --> 17:46.133
MOIRA:
Are you married, Mr. Wilson?

17:46.365 --> 17:48.242
Do you have any children?

17:49.068 --> 17:50.103
Certainly neither.

17:51.470 --> 17:54.974
Well, there must be someone special
in your life.

17:55.141 --> 17:56.142
[SIGHS]

17:56.309 --> 17:58.255
There was.

17:58.411 --> 18:00.618
But she passed away a few years ago.

18:00.913 --> 18:01.983
MOIRA:
I'm sorry.

18:02.148 --> 18:07.325
My mother and I have had to deal
with a lot of loss, unfortunately.

18:07.486 --> 18:10.262
And eventually we learned...

18:10.890 --> 18:12.961
that you just have to move on.

18:17.296 --> 18:19.333
I don't believe that.

18:20.833 --> 18:24.838
You know, I heard that your family
has an affinity with the fine arts.

18:25.004 --> 18:30.682
Yes, my husband amassed quite the collection
of 19th century American landscapes.

18:30.910 --> 18:33.686
SLADE: I'd love to see them.
- Maybe another day.

18:34.680 --> 18:38.685
Ahem. We have some family business
that we need to discuss right now.

18:38.918 --> 18:39.953
I'm sorry.

18:40.119 --> 18:43.692
My son seems to have forgotten
all his manners. Heh.

18:43.856 --> 18:46.530
Let me just get my staff
to open up the rest of the house.

18:46.692 --> 18:48.330
Thank you.

18:52.031 --> 18:53.203
[OLIVER GRUNTS]

18:54.934 --> 18:56.538
Mom?

18:56.769 --> 18:57.873
Ollie?

18:58.037 --> 18:59.710
Not yet, kid.

18:59.872 --> 19:02.716
I'm still to meet the rest of your family.

19:09.548 --> 19:10.618
Hello'?

19:15.121 --> 19:18.796
Hey, Ollie, have you and Mom talked?
Because this whole not speaking thing...

19:18.991 --> 19:21.471
- Thea, now is not a good time.
- Who is your friend?

19:22.061 --> 19:23.870
Slade Wilson.

19:24.030 --> 19:27.705
It's a pleasure to meet you. I've heard such
wonderful things from your mother. Heh, heh.

19:27.867 --> 19:30.711
- About me? Heh.
MOIRA: Thea.

19:30.870 --> 19:33.043
What perfect timing.
This is Slade Wilson...

19:33.205 --> 19:37.017
- They've met.
- and I was about to show him our collection.

19:37.176 --> 19:40.180
- But you're far better suited. Come.
THEA: Oh. Heh, heh.

19:43.015 --> 19:45.222
Senior year, I was obsessed with art.

19:45.384 --> 19:50.094
My teacher made me bring my entire art
history class over here to show our pieces.

19:50.256 --> 19:52.327
It was exactly as mortifying as it sounds.

19:52.525 --> 19:56.439
Oh, I'm sure it wasn't. You're a very
lucky girl to have known such privilege.

19:56.595 --> 20:00.543
And I'm fortunate
to have your entire family here. Heh.

20:06.272 --> 20:07.774
Oliver?

20:10.910 --> 20:12.856
Oliver, what's your name?

20:15.281 --> 20:17.090
Oliver Jonas Queen.

20:21.187 --> 20:22.791
Oliver, where were you born?

20:24.757 --> 20:26.634
Starling City.

20:27.693 --> 20:30.105
Why did you build a bonfire on the beach?

20:31.931 --> 20:34.104
So you'd see it.

20:35.101 --> 20:36.637
I told you.

20:37.737 --> 20:39.774
Was the bonfire a trap?

20:40.272 --> 20:43.151
Not a trap. It was a...

20:44.577 --> 20:46.488
A distraction.

20:48.814 --> 20:52.159
How was the bonfire a distraction?

20:53.786 --> 20:56.960
Where are Sara and Slade right now?

20:57.623 --> 20:59.330
Where are they?

21:01.827 --> 21:03.500
They're on the freighter.

21:05.498 --> 21:07.273
Where on the freighter?

21:10.002 --> 21:13.472
They're in the engine room,
because we have a raft.

21:13.672 --> 21:16.676
Sound the alarm. I want every man
on this freighter in that room.

21:16.842 --> 21:19.686
Search the entire floor. Go.

21:21.614 --> 21:23.616
Oliver Jonas Queen.

21:23.783 --> 21:25.319
[ALARM WAILING]

21:25.484 --> 21:27.088
THE BUTCHER:
You're with me.

21:28.687 --> 21:30.428
Secure all decks!

21:30.856 --> 21:32.358
SARA:
It'll taste even worse.

21:32.992 --> 21:34.528
But it'll work.

21:34.693 --> 21:38.038
I spent a year with Anthony Ivo.
I know how he thinks. It'll work.

21:38.197 --> 21:39.870
OLIVER:
And what is it, exactly?

21:40.032 --> 21:43.036
Cocculus indicus.
It's a natural source of picrotoxin...

21:43.202 --> 21:45.705
which will counteract
the effects of barbiturates.

21:45.871 --> 21:48.215
- Like sodium pentothal.
- Ivo's favorite.

21:48.374 --> 21:51.218
- But you still gotta act stoned to sell it.
- Lucky for me...

21:51.377 --> 21:53.379
before all this,
I had a lot of practice.

21:53.546 --> 21:55.048
[ALARM WAILING]

21:55.214 --> 21:56.989
[GRUNTING]

22:01.854 --> 22:03.663
SARA:
They're clearing the deck.

22:04.790 --> 22:06.235
The top of the ship's empty.

22:08.294 --> 22:09.398
Are you ready?

22:09.562 --> 22:11.872
You really don't want
an honest answer to that.

22:12.064 --> 22:14.738
You've done this before, right?

22:14.900 --> 22:16.402
- Nobody's done this before.
- Aah!

22:31.417 --> 22:34.091
Here. I think these belong to you.

22:34.653 --> 22:37.429
SLADE: We're on a clock,
and she needs to free the prisoners.

22:37.590 --> 22:40.070
Ivo sent his men to the engine room
like we planned.

22:40.226 --> 22:42.934
More convenient for me to take them out.

22:44.396 --> 22:45.431
Go find Iva.

22:45.698 --> 22:47.439
He can't get off this ship.

22:47.766 --> 22:49.609
But don't kill him.

22:50.603 --> 22:52.947
That son of a bitch is mine.

22:57.443 --> 23:00.515
And here we have a Curtis Swan from 1882.

23:00.679 --> 23:03.888
Fun fact about this one. He actually
painted it with his left hand...

23:04.049 --> 23:06.461
due to severe arthritis.

23:07.920 --> 23:10.799
- It's absolutely exquisite.
MOIRA: Mm-hm.

23:10.956 --> 23:14.927
I can't tell you how many offers we've had
from private collectors for it.

23:15.094 --> 23:19.804
But it was one of Dad's favorites.
Wasn't it, Ollie?

23:20.966 --> 23:22.775
Yes, it was.

23:23.469 --> 23:25.449
He loved that one.

23:25.604 --> 23:27.811
Then you must never sell it.

23:28.474 --> 23:32.149
I believe that
when we lose someone we love...

23:32.378 --> 23:34.984
we have the obligation
to honor their memory.

23:35.581 --> 23:37.151
[CHIMING]

23:43.789 --> 23:48.067
- You'd think eventually I'd hit something.
- Be patient. Ollie makes it look easy.

23:48.260 --> 23:50.171
Is anyone going to get that?

23:50.329 --> 23:52.639
I'll take that as a no. No worries.

23:52.798 --> 23:55.301
No matter where I go,
I'm just answering phones.

23:55.467 --> 23:56.969
Hello'?

23:57.670 --> 23:59.172
Oliver?

24:00.406 --> 24:03.012
Well, I do think we've been butt dialed.

24:03.275 --> 24:05.846
THEA [OVER SPEAKER]:
And here is a Joseph Kubert from 1890.

24:06.011 --> 24:07.820
Hey, that's Thea.

24:08.948 --> 24:10.689
SLADE [OVER SPEAKER]:
That's gorgeous.

24:10.849 --> 24:12.658
Wait, hold on.

24:13.185 --> 24:14.858
I know that voice.

24:15.020 --> 24:19.867
SLADE: I actually have a painting
from his first solo exhibition in Boston.

24:20.359 --> 24:21.531
Oh, God, no.

24:21.827 --> 24:22.862
Who is that?

24:23.028 --> 24:25.372
His name is Slade Wilson.

24:25.531 --> 24:30.378
And unless we stop him, he's gonna
kill Oliver and his entire family.

24:34.873 --> 24:38.047
- We have to move. Now.
- Are you sure it was Slade Wilson?

24:38.210 --> 24:40.212
- I thought he was dead.
- I'm sure.

24:40.379 --> 24:42.484
That's not a voice I'd ever forget.

24:42.648 --> 24:44.787
What's the biggest gun
you've got down here?

24:46.719 --> 24:48.562
That might work.

24:49.555 --> 24:51.034
Might?

24:51.190 --> 24:52.863
He has the Mirakuru in him.

24:53.225 --> 24:54.533
So do I.

24:55.694 --> 24:57.674
Can I trust you?

25:00.165 --> 25:02.076
I'll be fine.

25:02.368 --> 25:04.678
Slade was a trained killer
before he was injected.

25:04.837 --> 25:07.408
You get the chance, you get a shot,
you put him down.

25:08.240 --> 25:10.083
Please save Oliver.

25:11.210 --> 25:13.713
[MEN YELLING]

25:18.083 --> 25:23.089
[MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

25:23.422 --> 25:24.594
Why are you doing this?

25:24.823 --> 25:25.893
I'm with Oliver now.

25:26.058 --> 25:29.198
- Why should I believe you?
Because you don't want to die. Go.

25:39.104 --> 25:40.549
[GASPING]

25:40.739 --> 25:43.345
You helped that maniac torture us.

25:48.280 --> 25:50.783
[GRUNTING]

25:50.949 --> 25:52.451
[GUNFIRE]

26:16.041 --> 26:17.315
[COUGHING]

26:19.378 --> 26:20.413
Follow me.

26:22.815 --> 26:26.388
MAN 1: Where's Ivo?
MAN 2: He's heading to the bridge.

26:43.068 --> 26:45.844
[GUNFIRE]

26:51.743 --> 26:53.518
[GRUNTING]

26:58.684 --> 26:59.685
Answer the phone.

26:59.852 --> 27:00.922
[LINE RINGING]

27:01.086 --> 27:02.360
Please.

27:03.422 --> 27:04.696
JESSICA [OVER PHONE]:
Hello?

27:04.857 --> 27:06.336
Jessica, it's me.

27:06.492 --> 27:08.028
JESSICA:
Who?

27:08.627 --> 27:10.368
It's Anthony.

27:10.629 --> 27:12.267
JESSICA:
Anthony.

27:12.498 --> 27:14.978
I was married to a boy named Anthony.

27:15.134 --> 27:17.546
- I know, sweetheart.
JESSICA: But he went away.

27:17.803 --> 27:20.044
I went to find a cure.

27:20.539 --> 27:22.143
And I found one, sweetheart.

27:22.541 --> 27:23.781
I found it. And soon...

27:23.942 --> 27:25.387
[GUNFIRE THEN MAN YELLS]

27:25.611 --> 27:27.613
JESSICA:
He was a doctor.

27:27.779 --> 27:30.055
But he went away.

27:35.554 --> 27:38.296
[GROANS THEN COUGHS]

27:44.029 --> 27:46.236
It's harder than it looks, isn't it?

27:46.398 --> 27:47.809
Ah.

27:47.966 --> 27:49.843
Killing an unarmed man.

27:50.002 --> 27:53.006
Seemed pretty easy
when you murdered Shado.

27:53.205 --> 27:56.243
- I didn't murder her, Oliver.
- Ivo, you shot her in the head.

27:56.475 --> 27:58.421
I gave you a choice.

27:58.577 --> 28:00.853
You chose Sara.

28:01.713 --> 28:02.919
You blame me.

28:03.248 --> 28:06.024
But that's because you can't face
your own guilt.

28:06.518 --> 28:10.091
I loaded the bullets, yes.
I pulled the trigger.

28:11.723 --> 28:13.259
But you...

28:13.759 --> 28:15.534
You aimed the gun.

28:17.529 --> 28:20.271
And you hold yourself responsible.

28:20.566 --> 28:21.601
Don't you?

28:24.102 --> 28:25.581
Yes.

28:27.873 --> 28:30.217
That doesn't mean I won't kill you.

28:31.376 --> 28:33.447
The question is...

28:34.780 --> 28:36.555
what will he do'?

28:55.300 --> 28:56.472
Is it true?

29:00.138 --> 29:02.311
Tell me.

29:02.541 --> 29:05.317
- Slade, I tried to tell you...
- Tell him, Oliver.

29:06.645 --> 29:07.988
I was angry.

29:08.146 --> 29:10.319
Like you are right now.

29:10.582 --> 29:13.153
- I wasn't thinking clearly.
- Shut up.

29:13.752 --> 29:17.825
I acted rashly. I told him to choose
between Shado and Sara.

29:18.657 --> 29:19.761
OLIVER:
Don't listen to him.

29:19.958 --> 29:23.269
He's a monster. He will say anything.
You know that he will.

29:23.662 --> 29:25.266
IVO:
Tell him I'm lying, Oliver.

29:25.831 --> 29:27.504
Say it.

29:29.668 --> 29:30.840
I can explain.

29:32.004 --> 29:33.847
You chose.

29:40.679 --> 29:42.522
[BEEPING]

29:50.822 --> 29:52.358
[SHIP CREAKING]

29:54.126 --> 29:55.696
Slade.

29:56.361 --> 29:57.965
Please. Iva...

29:58.597 --> 30:00.338
He's dead.

30:00.699 --> 30:02.701
As dead as you are.

30:19.051 --> 30:21.224
[MEN YELLING]

30:49.748 --> 30:50.920
How many?

30:55.253 --> 30:58.666
This one time, you can pray for me.

31:14.206 --> 31:15.776
Behind you!

31:23.548 --> 31:26.392
Ollie, are you okay? Where's Slade?

31:27.285 --> 31:28.559
He knows.

31:31.123 --> 31:33.933
MAN:
Get down, get down!

31:35.394 --> 31:37.772
- We gotta get off this ship.
- No.

31:37.929 --> 31:41.274
Ollie, it's over. it's over. We gotta go.

31:41.466 --> 31:43.571
We can still swim back to the island.

31:43.735 --> 31:46.443
She's right, my friend.
We must hurry.

32:07.058 --> 32:10.335
Unh. Slade, wait.

32:17.736 --> 32:19.943
THE BUTCHER:
Stop. Don't move.

32:21.740 --> 32:23.947
Get in the cell.

32:26.178 --> 32:28.317
I do not take orders from you.

32:28.513 --> 32:30.993
I am this ship's captain.

32:36.321 --> 32:38.198
Not anymore.

32:43.361 --> 32:45.864
This is my ship now.

32:47.666 --> 32:49.873
Any objections?

33:00.378 --> 33:04.349
Slade Wilson is dangerous.
No chances. No mistakes.

33:06.785 --> 33:08.025
I'm in position.

33:08.353 --> 33:10.993
When Slade comes out,
I'll have the shot.

33:13.191 --> 33:15.797
FELICITY:
Thermal imaging's coming up now.

33:17.496 --> 33:18.736
They're in the northwest hall.

33:22.667 --> 33:25.580
SARA [OVER COMM]: Roy, remember,
just get Thea and Moira away from Slade.

33:25.737 --> 33:28.343
Don't start a fight. You'll lose. Okay?

33:28.507 --> 33:30.009
Okay.

33:30.408 --> 33:32.081
SARA:
Let's go.

33:54.599 --> 33:56.772
SLADE:
Ha-ha-ha. Thank you again...

33:57.002 --> 34:01.280
- for such a wonderful and insightful tour.
- Of course.

34:01.439 --> 34:02.850
You were a remarkable guide.

34:03.008 --> 34:04.749
Did you have a favorite?

34:05.110 --> 34:07.454
I found The Promise...

34:07.679 --> 34:09.625
to be particularly; compelling.

34:09.848 --> 34:11.020
ROY:
Thea? You home?

34:11.683 --> 34:14.357
Roy? I thought I was
meeting you at verdant.

34:14.953 --> 34:16.398
Oh, yeah.

34:18.255 --> 34:20.735
- Uh, this is, uh...
- I'm Roy Harper.

34:21.693 --> 34:23.070
Slade Wilson.

34:24.563 --> 34:27.304
That's a particularly firm handshake
you have there, son.

34:27.766 --> 34:29.074
Yeah, you too.

34:29.301 --> 34:30.905
[SLADE CHUCKLES]

34:36.975 --> 34:38.045
Ollie.

34:38.944 --> 34:40.719
There you are.

34:41.713 --> 34:44.056
Sara, we didn't hear you come in.

34:44.215 --> 34:46.752
I didn't want to interrupt the tour.

34:47.719 --> 34:51.496
MOIRA: Mr. Wilson, this is
my son's friend, Sara Lance.

34:51.656 --> 34:53.431
Of course.

34:54.426 --> 34:56.838
You're the girl who came
back from the dead.

34:57.295 --> 34:59.775
We're just glad to have her home.

35:00.599 --> 35:02.010
Oh, I can see.

35:02.233 --> 35:06.238
It's hard to find that special someone
who means everything to you.

35:07.005 --> 35:09.178
You're very lucky.

35:15.747 --> 35:17.158
So...

35:18.650 --> 35:21.153
what would you like to do now...

35:22.320 --> 35:24.095
Mr. Wilson?

35:36.768 --> 35:39.044
Well, I hate to break up the party...

35:40.105 --> 35:42.381
but I think I should be going.
MOIRA: Hmm.

35:42.874 --> 35:44.785
[SLADE & MOIRA CHUCKLING]

35:46.011 --> 35:49.220
- I look forward to seeing more of you, Moira.
- Oh.

35:52.884 --> 35:55.057
And your lovely family.

35:57.122 --> 35:59.898
Dig's got a shot lined up outside.

36:00.191 --> 36:01.795
OLIVER:
Mr. Wilson.

36:03.028 --> 36:05.065
May I walk you to your car?

36:22.647 --> 36:24.183
Cyrus Gold...

36:24.382 --> 36:27.659
the man in the skull mask.
All this was you.

36:28.520 --> 36:30.193
They worked for you.

36:30.922 --> 36:33.425
Well, I have my allies.

36:33.658 --> 36:36.002
Just as you have yours.

36:36.695 --> 36:38.106
John Diggle, for example.

36:38.997 --> 36:43.104
I suppose you're wondering
why he hasn't taken his head shot.

36:45.403 --> 36:47.076
Don't worry.

36:47.439 --> 36:48.509
He's still alive.

36:49.074 --> 36:50.781
For now.

36:53.011 --> 36:54.456
Slade.

36:59.084 --> 37:01.257
What do you want?

37:02.620 --> 37:04.224
SLADE:
Hmm.

37:11.262 --> 37:14.266
Five years ago, I made you a promise.

37:14.466 --> 37:15.604
Do you remember?

37:18.603 --> 37:21.083
Well, I'm here to fulfill it.

37:21.773 --> 37:24.151
I'll see you around, kid.

37:36.588 --> 37:37.658
We made it.

37:37.822 --> 37:39.927
[SARA GASPING AND PANTING]

37:40.391 --> 37:42.166
Where's Oliver?

37:46.998 --> 37:48.841
[DOOR OPENS]

37:55.440 --> 37:57.852
I need you to see something.

38:08.686 --> 38:10.757
Okay. Wait.

38:12.590 --> 38:13.864
You need me.

38:14.025 --> 38:15.834
Okay? You have the Mirakuru in you.

38:16.628 --> 38:18.767
Not just in me.

38:24.936 --> 38:28.042
You burned a box full of dirt.

38:28.473 --> 38:31.283
IVO: Okay, look.
I can help you understand how it works.

38:31.476 --> 38:34.946
- I've spent my entire life studying it, all right?
- It was you.

38:35.647 --> 38:37.456
You were the one who killed Shado.

38:37.982 --> 38:39.017
No.

38:39.184 --> 38:42.393
No, he chose. It was him.

38:48.359 --> 38:50.305
Give him your gun.

38:52.497 --> 38:54.067
Take it.

38:55.567 --> 38:57.240
And show me...

38:57.969 --> 38:59.539
how you killed Shado.

39:00.171 --> 39:02.082
Show me!

39:09.347 --> 39:10.985
Slade.

39:13.718 --> 39:14.856
This isn't you.

39:17.155 --> 39:19.101
It's the Mirakuru...

39:19.257 --> 39:20.327
and you're sick.

39:21.392 --> 39:22.530
I don't care.

39:22.727 --> 39:24.934
I was trying to protect Sara.

39:27.432 --> 39:32.006
But I didn't want Shado to die. I cared
for her too, and you know that I did.

39:32.737 --> 39:34.580
I don't care.

39:37.575 --> 39:39.851
You said we were brothers.

39:40.879 --> 39:42.722
You said that.

39:44.582 --> 39:45.754
Is that how you did it?

39:46.251 --> 39:50.063
- Is that how you pointed the gun at her?
- Yes.

39:57.929 --> 39:59.465
[SCREAMING]

40:01.699 --> 40:03.235
Get him out of here.

40:07.705 --> 40:09.742
Why don't you just kill me?

40:09.908 --> 40:11.751
If I kill you now...

40:13.044 --> 40:14.921
it would be a mercy.

40:17.782 --> 40:19.659
You cannot die...

40:20.485 --> 40:22.487
until you have suffered...

40:24.088 --> 40:26.659
the same way that I have suffered.

40:27.825 --> 40:29.964
Until you have known...

40:30.995 --> 40:32.303
complete despair.

40:33.498 --> 40:35.273
And you will.

40:37.168 --> 40:39.114
I promise.

40:48.479 --> 40:50.117
MOIRA:
Mr. Wilson leave?

40:50.281 --> 40:51.851
Yeah.

40:54.118 --> 40:56.598
- It's getting pretty late. I'm gonna go too.
- Mm.

40:56.754 --> 40:58.427
Oliver.

40:59.023 --> 41:03.995
I know you and I have our differences, but
they hardly excuse your behavior tonight.

41:08.166 --> 41:12.774
If this is the way you're gonna act around me
from now on, then don't come by the house.

41:44.235 --> 41:45.578
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

42:17.068 --> 42:19.070
[English - US - SDH]
